    {
      "datetime": "2026-05-11T16:12:53Z",
      "kind": "Normal",
      "repo": "packages/apps/DeskClock",
      "title": "DeskClock: Fix bottom navigation label clipping in landscape",
      "description": "The Material 3 Expressive migration in f4e0e040a updated the portrait\nBottomNavigationView to wrap_content (letting the library size each item\nvia its M3 tokens, with an 80dp item minimum) but only refreshed the\nbackground attribute in res/layout-land/desk_clock.xml, leaving the\nM2-era android:layout_height=\"72dp\" in place.\n\nSince the M3 NavigationBarItemView's default minimum height (~80dp)\nexceeds 72dp, each item's label TextView is clipped at the parent\nboundary, cutting off the lower half of \"Alarm/Clock/Timer/Stopwatch\"\nlabels on the landscape layout.\n\nApply the same wrap_content fix that portrait already received, so both\nlayouts defer sizing to the Material library.",
      "author_name": "cynagenautes",
      "author_email": "rainlinbolt2001@gmail.com",
      "change_id": "Ica7263bcaa95c32244e52d654d5e6196d24694e3",
      "commit": "23107f7f51a16d4787f5e5fe7e357234d018ed1d",
      "commit_url": "https://github.com/LineageOS/android_packages_apps_DeskClock/commit/23107f7f51a1",
      "review_url": "https://review.lineageos.org/q/Ica7263bcaa95c32244e52d654d5e6196d24694e3"
    },
